<paragraph id="777236A6703B962AF91DFC60FE09BD60" blockId="7.[263,1555,1001,1097]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
The following key should allow separation of males of 
<taxonomicName id="B0CD4D25703B962AF970FBADFE16BD60" authorityName="Garrison" authorityYear="1982" box="[265,490,1057,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Archilestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Archilestes</taxonomicName>
:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3FD7652D703B9625F9FCFBE2FA88BE56" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="key">
<key id="035C6197703B962AF9FCFBE2F9E1B1A0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyStep id="CC392E03703B962AF9FCFBE2F9E7BF9C" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<paragraph id="777236A6703B962AF9FCFBE2F9E6BCE7" blockId="7.[388,1563,1130,1488]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="CC3C9593703B962AF9FCFBE2F9E6BCE7" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
1. Marginal cell posterior to subtriangle in hindwing enlarged at border so that anal border of wing is strongly convex (
<bibRefCitation id="135C4B57703B962AFB54FB59FB6BBDD4" author="Williamson" box="[813,1175,1237,1277]" firstAuthor="Williamson" journalOrPublisher="Occ.Pap. Mus. Zool. Univ. Mich." pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 9" part="96" refId="ref4277" refString="WILLIAMSON, E. B. 1921. Two new neotropical genera of Lestinae (Odonata). Occ-. Pap. Mus. Zool. Univ. Mich., 96 1 - 9." title="Two new neotropical genera of Lestinae (Odonata)" type="journal article" year="1921">Williamson 1921</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 1; 
<bibRefCitation id="135C4B57703B962AFD23FB59FDE2BC1B" author="Donnelly" firstAuthor="Donnelly" journalOrPublisher="Fla. Entomol." pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="412 - 417" part="64" refId="ref3970" refString="DONNELLY, T. W. 1. 1981. A new species of Archilestes ~ from Mexico and Central America, with further notes on tlie status of Cyptolestes Williamson (Odonata: Lestidae). Fla. Entomol., 64: 412 - 417." title="A new species of Archilestes from Mexico and Central America, with further notes on tlie status of Cyptolestes Williamson (Odonata: Lestidae)" type="journal article" year="1981">Donnelly 1981</bibRefCitation>
, Figs. 3, 5). Broadening ratio (length of distal vein of marginal cell posterior to subtriangle in hind wing relative to that of forewing) 1.23 or more (subgenus 
<emphasis id="45B9EAB4703B962AF9C5FA2AFD4ABCE7" box="[444,694,1446,1486]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName id="B0CD4D25703B962AF9C5FA2AFD5BBCE7" authorityName="Williamson" authorityYear="1921" box="[444,679,1446,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Odonata (awaiting allocation)" genus="Cyptolestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cyptolestes</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="777236A6703B962AF901FA7EF9E7BF9C" blockId="7.[375,1563,1519,1719]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="CC3C9593703B962AF901FA7EF9E7BF9C" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
1'. Marginal cell posterior to subquadrangle in hind wing not greatly enlarged at border, anal border of wing gently convex (
<bibRefCitation id="135C4B57703B962AFB7BF9D6FB97BFAB" author="Williamson" box="[770,1131,1626,1666]" firstAuthor="Williamson" journalOrPublisher="Occ.Pap. Mus. Zool. Univ. Mich." pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 9" part="96" refId="ref4277" refString="WILLIAMSON, E. B. 1921. Two new neotropical genera of Lestinae (Odonata). Occ-. Pap. Mus. Zool. Univ. Mich., 96 1 - 9." title="Two new neotropical genera of Lestinae (Odonata)" type="journal article" year="1921">Williamson 1921</bibRefCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="45B9EAB4703B962AFCFCF9D6FB32BFAB" box="[1157,1230,1626,1666]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig</emphasis>
. 2); broadening ratio 1.20 or less (subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="B0CD4D25703B962AFC70F901FB19BF9C" authority="Garrison, 1982" authorityName="Garrison" authorityYear="1982" box="[1033,1253,1677,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Archilestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto" status="s.s.">Archilestes</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="45B9EAB4703B962AFC81F901FABBBF9C" box="[1272,1351,1677,1717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="5E8A57CF703B962AFC81F901FAC9BF9C" box="[1272,1333,1677,1717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
)
</emphasis>
...... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="CC392E03703B962AF929F952F9E1B1A0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<paragraph id="777236A6703B962AF929F952F9E6BE89" blockId="7.[334,1566,1752,1954]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="CC3C9593703B962AF929F952F9E6BE89" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
2(1). T i p of superior appendage blunt, truncate (
<figureCitation id="EFF62A23703B962AFD00F952F9E9BE2F" box="[1401,1557,1758,1798]" captionStart="Figures 10-24" captionStartId="5.[292,401,2104,2134]" captionTargetBox="[202,1306,405,2323]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 10-24. Male structures of Archilestes: 10-21, ventral and latel-alvlews of penes; 22-24, dorsal views of male abdominal appendages; 10-1 1,Archtlrstrs cali/ornzca, male. California: Solano Co.; 12-13, A. grandis, male. Venezuela: Miranda State; 14-15, A. latialatus, male. Mexico: Veracruz; 16-17, A, tuberalatus, male. T'enezuela: Aragua State; 18-19, A. exoletus, male. Argentina: Misiones Province; 20-21, A. rrgalis, male. Mexico: San Luis Potosi; 22, A. latialatus, paratype. Guatemala: Alta T'erapaz Province; 23, A. latialatus. Mexico: Veracruz; 24, A. latialatus. Costa Rica: Alajuela Province." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3535434" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3535434/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="135C4B57703B962AF9C4F883FCCDBE1E" author="Williamson" box="[445,817,1807,1847]" firstAuthor="Williamson" journalOrPublisher="Occ.Pap. Mus. Zool. Univ. Mich." pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 9" part="96" refId="ref4277" refString="WILLIAMSON, E. B. 1921. Two new neotropical genera of Lestinae (Odonata). Occ-. Pap. Mus. Zool. Univ. Mich., 96 1 - 9." title="Two new neotropical genera of Lestinae (Odonata)" type="journal article" year="1921">Williamson 1921</bibRefCitation>
); Rg arising from R p before third postnodal crossvein in 
<emphasis id="45B9EAB4703B962AFBD8F8CFFBABBE42" box="[929,1111,1859,1899]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">forewing</emphasis>
; states of Aragua and Carabobo, Northern Venezuela ......... tuberalatus
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="777236A6703B962AF911F84FF9E1B1A0" blockId="7.[358,401,1987,2030]" lastBlockId="7.[444,1574,1986,2186]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="CC3C9593703B962AF911F84FF9E1B1A0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
2'. T i p of superior appendage acute (
<figureCitation id="EFF62A23703B962AFCBAF849FA4EBEC4" box="[1219,1458,1989,2029]" captionStart="Figures 10-24" captionStartId="5.[292,401,2104,2134]" captionTargetBox="[202,1306,405,2323]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 10-24. Male structures of Archilestes: 10-21, ventral and latel-alvlews of penes; 22-24, dorsal views of male abdominal appendages; 10-1 1,Archtlrstrs cali/ornzca, male. California: Solano Co.; 12-13, A. grandis, male. Venezuela: Miranda State; 14-15, A. latialatus, male. Mexico: Veracruz; 16-17, A, tuberalatus, male. T'enezuela: Aragua State; 18-19, A. exoletus, male. Argentina: Misiones Province; 20-21, A. rrgalis, male. Mexico: San Luis Potosi; 22, A. latialatus, paratype. Guatemala: Alta T'erapaz Province; 23, A. latialatus. Mexico: Veracruz; 24, A. latialatus. Costa Rica: Alajuela Province." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3535434" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3535434/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Figs. 22-24</figureCitation>
); R3 arising from R2 at 
<emphasis id="45B9EAB4703B962AFB2FF874FC74B109" box="[854,904,2040,2080]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">or</emphasis>
, more often, beyond third postnodal crossvein in forewing; southern Mexico to Costa Rica.................................. latialatus
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
<keyStep id="CC392E03703B9625F93AF722FA8DB8F3" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<key id="035C6197703B9625F93AF722FA8DB8F3" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<paragraph id="777236A6703B962AF93AF722F9E7B020" blockId="7.[322,1563,2217,2316]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead id="CC3C9593703B962AF93AF722F9E7B020" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">3(1'). Vein Rg arising from R2 beyond second postnodal crossvein in both fore- and hind wings .......... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="777236A670349625F8A9FEF2FA8DB8F3" blockId="8.[208,246,379,422]" lastBlockId="8.[279,1393,379,477]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<keyLead id="CC3C959370349625F8A9FEF2FA8DB8F3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
3'. Vein 
<emphasis id="45B9EAB470349625F9FFFEF2FE4DB88F" bold="true" box="[390,433,382,422]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Rg</emphasis>
arising at or before second postnodal crossvein in both wings ................................. 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</key>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="CC392E0370349625F8D0FE73FA8EBA83" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<key id="035C619770349625F8D0FE73FA8EBA83" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<paragraph id="777236A670349625F8D0FE73FA8CBBEA" blockId="8.[169,1392,507,710]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<keyLead id="CC3C959370349625F8D0FE73FA8CBBEA" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
4(3). Vein 
<emphasis id="45B9EAB470349625F9FDFE73FE53BB0E" bold="true" box="[388,431,511,551]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Rg</emphasis>
arising at or before fourth postnodal crossvein in both wings; pterothorax largely pale with no metallic green stripes; Southern Brazil, Northern Argentina ........................................ 
<taxonomicName id="B0CD4D2570349625FCB3FD10FA8CBBEA" box="[1226,1392,668,707]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exoletus">
<emphasis id="45B9EAB470349625FCB3FD10FA8CBBEA" box="[1226,1392,668,707]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">exoletus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="777236A670349625F8A8FD6BFA8EBA83" blockId="8.[209,246,741,783]" lastBlockId="8.[280,1397,740,941]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<keyLead id="CC3C959370349625F8A8FD6BFA8EBA83" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
4'. Vein Rg arising from R2before fourth postnodal crossvein in both wings; pterothorax with broad stripe of metallic green on mesepimeron and mesepisternum (
<bibRefCitation id="135C4B5770349625F951FC0FFDE3BA82" author="Gloyd" box="[296,543,899,939]" firstAuthor="Gloyd" journalOrPublisher="Occ.Pap. Mus. Zool. Univ. Mich." pageId="8" pageNumber="9" part="485" refId="ref4018" refString="GLOYD, L. K. 1944. A new species of Archilestes from Mexico (Odonata: Lestinae). Occ. I'ap. Mus. Zool. I! niv. Mich., 485: l- 4" title="A new species of Archilestes from Mexico (Odonata: Lestinae)" type="book" year="1944">Gloyd 1944</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 1); Northeastern Mexico.. 
<taxonomicName id="B0CD4D2570349625FC94FC0FFA8EBA83" authorityName="Gloyd" authorityYear="1944" box="[1261,1394,899,938]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Archilestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="regalis">
<emphasis id="45B9EAB470349625FC94FC0FFA8EBA83" box="[1261,1394,899,938]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">regalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</key>
</keyStep>
<key id="035C619770349625F8D4FC43FA88BE56" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<keyStep id="CC392E0370349625F8D4FC43FA84BC9B" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<paragraph id="777236A670349625F8D4FC43FA8CBDB8" blockId="8.[173,1396,972,1174]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<keyLead id="CC3C959370349625F8D4FC43FA8CBDB8" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
5(3). Posterior half of superior appendages greatly expanded, truncate and leaf-like in appearance (Figs. 7, 9); large species, abdomen excluding appendages 55 mm, hind wing 42 mm; Costa Rica ................. 
<taxonomicName id="B0CD4D2570349625FCA3FBE6FA8CBDB8" authorityName="Garrison" authorityYear="1982" box="[1242,1392,1130,1169]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Archilestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neblina">
<emphasis id="45B9EAB470349625FCA3FBE6FA8CBDB8" box="[1242,1392,1130,1169]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">neblina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="777236A670349625F8ACFB35FA84BC9B" blockId="8.[175,1401,1205,1689]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<keyLead id="CC3C959370349625F8ACFB35FA84BC9B" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">5'. Posterior half of superior appendages linear, similar in width to basal half of appendages (Pritchard and Smith&quot; 1956, Fig. 4.62); smaller species, abdomen excluding appendages less than 50 mm, hind wing less than 40 mm ................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="CC392E0370349625F8C9FA59FA88BE56" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<paragraph id="777236A670349625F8C9FA59FA8BBFBE" blockId="8.[175,1401,1205,1689]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<keyLead id="CC3C959370349625F8C9FA59FA8BBFBE" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
6(5). Inferior a b d o m i n a l appendages parallel-sided (Pritchard and Smith 1956, 
<emphasis id="45B9EAB470349625FBFCF985FC30BF18" box="[901,972,1545,1585]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig</emphasis>
. 4.62), mesepimeral stripe never metallic; Washington, Oregon, California, Baja California ....................... 
<taxonomicName id="B0CD4D2570349625FCE6F9FCFA8BBFBE" authorityName="McLachlan" authorityYear="1895" box="[1183,1399,1648,1687]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Archilestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="californica">
<emphasis id="45B9EAB470349625FCE6F9FCFA8BBFBE" box="[1183,1399,1648,1687]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">californica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="777236A670349625F8A1F930FA88BE56" blockId="8.[214,1400,1721,1921]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<keyLead id="CC3C959370349625F8A1F930FA88BE56" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
6'. Inferior abdominal appendages divergent, not parallelsided (Pritchard and Smith 1956, Fig. 4.62); dark mesepimeral stripe often metallic green; United States south to Colombia and Venezuela......... 
<taxonomicName id="B0CD4D2570349625FCA6F8D4FA88BE56" box="[1247,1396,1880,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis id="45B9EAB470349625FCA6F8D4FA88BE56" box="[1247,1396,1880,1919]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
